{# Neutral placeholder mark, derived from the client's own business name so
   it's never wrong for a given vertical — swap for the client's real logo
   before launch (see the re-skin checklist). Takes `name` explicitly rather
   than reading `site` implicitly, since this macro is imported without
   `with context` at its call sites. #}
{% macro render(className, name) %}<svg class="{{ className }}" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="11" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/><text x="12" y="12.5" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" fill="currentColor" font-family="ui-serif, Georgia, serif" font-size="12">{{ name | first | upper }}</text></svg>{% endmacro %}
